Document: AnimationNodeAdd3  
Path: godot/classes/class_animationnodeadd3.rst  
Summary: Class AnimationNodeAdd3 reference section.  

Class: AnimationNodeAdd3  
inherits from AnimationNode  
This node is used to add 3D animations to a scene. It allows for the addition of animations to a scene tree, enabling the animation of 3D models. The node provides a way to control the playback of animations, including the ability to loop, play, and stop animations. It also allows for the adjustment of animation parameters such as speed and blend weight. The node can be connected to other nodes in the scene tree to control the animation of multiple objects simultaneously. Key Rule: This node is specifically designed for 3D animations and may not work correctly with 2D animations.
